By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) – Governor Ben Ayade of Cross River has lost his bid to return to the Senate when he concludes his two-term next year. The governor joined the ruling All Progressives Congress in 2021 and took part in the ruling party’s Senate primary in Calabar. Results of the primary show Mr Ayade polled 52 votes to crash out against Adams Cecelia, who scored 140. Another aspirant Martin Orim scored 61 votes. However, there are other Governors and other party members who have secured their ticket to contest for governorship positions in the some states under the platform of the All Progressives Congress. List of APC successful candidates are as follows: By EMMANUEL MOGBEDE ABUJA- The All Progressives Congress (APC) has adjusted its special convention for presidential primary earlier scheduled for May 29-30 to June 6-8.Mr Felix Morka, the party’s National Publicity Secretary, announced this in a statement on Saturday in Abuja.“This   follows the Independent National Electoral Commission’s extension of deadline… In "Politics" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Cross River State Governor, Sen. Ben Ayade has described the Transportation Minister, Rt Hon. Chibuike Rotimi Amaechi as a man with outstanding qualities fit to rule Nigeria. The RT Hon. Chibuike Rotimi Amaechi Media Office disclosed this in a statement made available to… In "Top Stories" First, it started like rumour weeks back, when news filtered in that former President Goodluck Jonathan was considering a return to Aso Rock. The rumour mill went agog as his posters began appearing in some cities across the country and later assumed a life of its own at the weekend… In "Interview"